<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 02 at 3:40PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Sequoyah and south central Adair Counties through 415 PM CDT...
At 339 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
west of Sallisaw, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and dime to penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Sallisaw...                       Marble City...
Brushy Lake State Park...         Brushy...
Mc Key...
This includes Interstate 40 in Oklahoma between mile markers 300 and
306.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
